e3 Nbd7 9. Be2 ({This looks less active than} 9. Bd3 {, which is examined in
the next line, but White hopes to activate his bishop via f3.}) 9... h6 10. Bh4
g5 11. Bg3 h5 $1 {The typical pseudo pawn sacrifice, ensuring Black
considerable kingside progress.} 12. h4 {The most principled continuation,
involving a pawn sacrifice, though.} (12. h3 {just weakens the kingside.} Ne4
13. Qc2 Qe7 14. b4 {Nestorovic,D (2365)-Bogdanovski,V (2515) Belgrade 1994 
