Bd7 23. f3 gxf3 24. Qxf3 Ng4 25. Qxf7 Qxf7 26. Rxf7 Kc8 $17 {After ... Kb7
Black will be perfectly regrouped and with the better structure.}) 13... Bxg2
14. Rg1 Bb7 15. Qa4 (15. Qc2 {does not challenge Black in any way.} Qe7 16.
O-O-O O-O-O 17. b4 Kb8 18. Kb2 Ne8 $146 19. Rc1 f6 20. Ne4 e5 $17) 15... Qe7
16. O-O-O Kd8 $5 $146 {A familiar manoeuvre, proving that White's positional
