(2540) -Zhidkov,V (2400) Nizhnij Tagil 1998 (1/2-1/2, 47)} Bh6 24. Rh3 Nh5 25.
Ng4 Bg7 26. d5 Nf4 27. Qd2 Nxh3+ 28. gxh3 f5 29. Nf6+ Bxf6 30. Bxf6 Re8 31.
dxe6 Qc6 32. Qd5 Qc7 33. Qb5 Qc6 34. Qxc6 Rxc6 35. c5 bxc5 36. Bc4 Ba6 37. Bd5
Rd6 38. Re5 Rxd5 39. Rxd5 Rxe6 40. Bc3 $11) 16... Bf8 17. Qe3 g6 18. h3 {
1/2-1/2 Napalkov,V (2511)-Shulman,B (2431) ICCF email 2017} Bxf3 $5 (18... Bg7
$11) 19. Qxf3 Bh6 20. Rcd1 Bxd2 21. Rxd2 Qxc4 22. d5 Nxd5 23. Bb3 Qh4 24. Bxd5
exd5 25. Rxe8+ Rxe8 26. Rxd5 Qe7 27. Qf4 f6 {White has just reasonable
compensation for the pawn due to Black's king's relative vulnerability, but no
more than that.} *

